headline: Marc Andreessen’s a16z Invests $465 Million in Navan’s Corporate Spending Platform, According to Recent SEC Filing
summary: a16z Capital Management, the venture firm founded by Marc Andreessen and Ben Horowitz, committed $465 million to Navan, backing its expansion from corporate travel booking into integrated enterprise spending and payments.

headline: Block Bets On AI And Bitcoin To Rekindle Growth Story
summary: Block, Inc. (NYSE:XYZ) has launched Square AI in the UK as a free, conversational assistant for small and medium businesses. The tool is designed to help merchants make faster, data driven decisions using their existing Square data. Cash App has also updated its Bitcoin fee and withdrawal structure, targeting broader cryptocurrency use across its user base. Block is rolling out these product updates while its share price sits at $50.81, with the stock showing a 22.0% decline year to date...

headline: Trump Jr. calls banking a 'Ponzi scheme' that forced family to create crypto business
summary: Donald Trump Jr. and Eric Trump are hosting the World Liberty Forum at the Mar-a-Lago club in Palm Beach, Fla., owned by their father, President Donald Trump.
